Last-known GitHub WS3D tip: `f9475db0a5843215134fc29409ce4dd2f0a266b0` (PR #52 merge — still cached locally as `origin/main`).

### Do NOT email GitHub Support to wait for restore

Local coverage of the deleted repo is **100%**:

| Metric | C: WS3D | E: WS3D |
|--------|---------|---------|
| `origin/main` SHA matches GitHub's last tip | ✅ `f9475db` | ✅ `f9475db` |
| `origin/*` remote refs (branches) | 38 | 38 |
| All previously missing commits (f9475db, 444663f, 11640f7, 8a36cea, c44ae08) present | ✅ | ✅ |
| `branch -r` parity between C: and E: | ✅ identical | ✅ identical |
| Reachability of all commits via local refs | ✅ | ✅ |
| Diff `origin/main` vs `origin/main` (self-check) | 0 lines | 0 lines |

E: WS3D was originally missing 14 `origin/*` refs (it was on stale `origin/main` = `df3a92e`). These were restored via:
1. Re-bundled `wsm3d-full-backup.bundle` (173 MB) from C: with `git bundle create --all` (77 refs)
2. Fetched into E: with `git fetch --no-recurse-submodules C:/Users/koosh/_wsm3d_audit/wsm3d-full-backup.bundle "+refs/remotes/*:refs/remotes/*"` (the submodule fetch was failing on a detached SHA `46d9f94` from the old worktree Compound-Spheres — `--no-recurse-submodules` bypassed it)
3. Verified `cat-file -t f9475db c44ae08 444663f` returns `commit` in E:

